HB 681 Original 2026 Regular Session Hilferty
Abstract: Increases the maximum fee amount for a parcel fee authorized to be levied
within the Lakeview Crime Prevention District in Orleans Parish.
Present law creates the Lakeview Crime Prevention District in Orleans Parish as a political
subdivision to aid in crime prevention and add to the security of the district residents by
providing for an increase in the presence of law enforcement personnel in the district.
Provides for district boundaries, governance, and powers and duties.
Proposed law retains present law.
Present law authorizes the governing authority of the city of New Orleans, subject to voter
approval, to impose and collect a parcel fee within the district. Provides that the fee amount
shall be as requested by duly adopted resolution of the board, not to exceed $150 per parcel
per year. Requires that the fee be imposed on each parcel within the district, whether such
parcel is improved or unimproved.
Proposed law increases the maximum fee authorized to be imposed within the district from
$150 to $250 per parcel per year. Proposed law otherwise retains present law.
(Amends R.S. 33:9091.1(F)(1)(b))
